I don't think we should have a null check.
Instead of delegating to forEach, I think we should be delegating to putAll() which sometimes is better optimized (See UnifiedMap for an example).
Taken together, the implementation for all mutable maps will be:
this.putAll(map);
return this;
Which means the implementations can be pulled up to interfaces as default methods. AbstractMutable*Maps will be unchanged.

